== 0.4.5 2021-12-26

* Drop --ignore-cvs-lines as a default option.
  It now causes the "Regular expression too big" error on macOS Monterey.

== 0.4.4 2021-04-06

* Fix a fatal conflict when -p is specified.
  ("error: conflicting output format options.")

== 0.4.3 2015-01-05

* Do not use colors if the terminal does not support colors.

* Do not invoke a pager when on a dumb terminal.

== 0.4.2 2013-08-16

* Do not close inherited file descriptors on invoking diff(1) so that
  `di file <(command)` works.

== 0.4.1 2013-04-11

* Set better labels and disable pager if invoked by git difftool.

* Enhance the --color option like Git.

== 0.4.0 2013-04-04

* Add inline word-diff highlighting.

* Improve suspicious whitespace highlighting.

== 0.3.2 2013-01-09

* Do not choke on encoding errors when colorizing on Ruby 1.9+.

== 0.3.1 2012-05-21

* Resurrect -L which Subversion still relies on.

== 0.3.0 2012-05-14

* Fix pagerizing with Ruby 1.9+ and turn it on by default.

* Complement a missing implementation of --unidirectional-new-file.

* Complement a missing implementation of -S/--starting-file=FILE.

* Add support for --suppress-blank-empty.

* Fix handling of -T/--initial-tab.

* Remove -L which use has long been deprecated.

== 0.2.3 2012-03-29

* Fix the case where comparing two directories fails when the latter
  contains a directory that the former doesn't have.

== 0.2.2 2012-01-18

* Try to fix a bug where "di DIR FILE..." produces a reversed diff.

== 0.2.1 2011-08-04

* Make the regexp pattern used for --ignore-cvs-lines more specific so
  it does not misfire on Perl scripts.

* Disable --pager on Ruby 1.9, which currently stalls.

== 0.2.0 2011-05-09

* Update the default exclude pattern list:
    - Sort out file patterns and directory patterns so that (for example)
      a directory named "core" is not ignored.
    - Remove RCSLOG and cvslog.* which I haven't seen for decades.
    - Add files generated by gtags(1): GTAGS, GRTAGS, GSYMS and GPATH.
    - Add core.<pid>.
    - Add *.so.<version>.
    - Add *.bundle and *.dylib for OS X.
    - Add *.py[co].

== 0.1.9 2010-05-06

* Make changes regarding file layout and documentation.

== 0.1.8 2010-03-11

* Fix unified diff parser.

== 0.1.7 2010-03-11

* Determine *_OPTIONS environment variable name by the executable file name.

== 0.1.6 2010-03-11

* Fix colorization of the last hunk.

* Reimplement --version.

== 0.1.5 2010-03-10

* Add --[no-]color and colorize diff output by default.

* Read user's preferred default options from DI_OPTIONS.

== 0.1.4 2010-03-10

* Add --[no-]pager and turn it on by default.

* Do not choke on file names starting with a hyphen.

== 0.1.3 2010-03-10

* Fix handling of the following options and make custom format options
  work:
    -D/--ifdef=NAME
    --GTYPE-group-format=GFMT
    --line-format=LFMT
    --LTYPE-line-format=LFMT

* Fix a problem where escape sequence ESC $ B .. : is regarded as CVS
  keyword, which often appears in a text encoded in ISO-2022-JP.

== 0.1.1 2008-10-06

* Initial release
